# Example .gitattributes for git-crypt-encrypted raw/ trees.
#
# Copy this file to `.gitattributes` and uncomment the lines for each
# L2 whose `raw/` tree should be encrypted at rest. Then run
# `bash _system/scripts/setup_encryption.sh` (which is also idempotent
# and can append these rules for you).
#
# Reference: docs/setup.md §"Privacy — sensitive material"

# domains/psychology/raw/**     filter=git-crypt diff=git-crypt
# domains/<your-sensitive-domain>/raw/**     filter=git-crypt diff=git-crypt
